    "For any x ∈ X, supposing that r i is the closest RP to x, the ML-Index adopts the following projection function,f (x) = dist(x, r i) + j<i max x ∈X j dist(x, r j), (1)whereX j = {x | r j is the closest RP to x ∧ x ∈ X }.Recall the iDistance computation, i.e., i Dist(x) = dist(x, r i)+i •C (with a large constant C) and r i is the closest RP to x.",
